    Vice President, Exhibitor Services, Sales and Business Development, International CES</p>
    <hr align="center" width="90%" size="1" noshade color="#999999">
    <!-- article start -->
    <p><strong>Ideas to Boost Your Marketing Strategy: Make Your Vision Last Year-Round</strong><br> by Dan Cole</p>
    <p>June is one of my favorite months. It’s when we at CEA kick-start our CES preparations for the coming year into high gear. It’s true that we work on the show year-round, and as an association, we’re here 365 days a year to help grow the consumer electronics (CE) industry. But, June marks the time that our attendee registration opens online and when we, as a staff, start our countdown to the big show.
<P>I am already incredibly excited for the 2008 International CES, and equally pleased to be working with each of our exhibitors to help make your experience better and better each year. In my last decade here at CEA, I have witnessed the transformation of CES into a worldwide stage ideally positioned to help promote your brands and products. Indeed, they are the best brands, products and people across the industry – from manufacturing and retailing to content creation and delivery.</P>
<P>One of the key strategies we employ to grow the show and extend its reach throughout the year is our year-round promotions plan. For us, CES isn’t just a January event. It’s the key starting point used to promote the industry everyday of the year. </P>
<P>The circulation of our<I> Vision</I> magazine includes the very top decision-makers from our CES attendee database. We then deliver insightful knowledge and exclusive research to these 23,000 readers throughout the year to make sure they know how they can grow their businesses both at the show and year-round. Magazine advertisers benefit by reaching global CE executives and reinforcing their brands and messaging across the CE spectrum.</P>
<P>We’ve also positioned the very valuable CES brand with other events around the world, like this past May’s Hometech in Dubai, U.A.E. and the July SINOCES in China. These international events let us extend the CES brand and help us bring new markets to our exhibitors and CEA members.</P>
<P>In October, we’ll bring some 500 key industry players together for the CEA Industry Forum in San Diego to rally around pivotal issues and future plans for the industry. Sponsorships at Industry Forum help service providers and other vendors reach targeted audiences.</P>
<P>How can this same strategy relate to your own CES preparations? Start first by thinking of your CES participation as more than just a booth. Your booth is a key element of how you can get the industry to love your company and products, but it’s just one element. How else are you promoting yourself? Are you applying to speak at any CES conference sessions? Are you sponsoring any targeted receptions or attendee services? Are you laying out a year-round advertising and PR campaign to build up anticipation for your booth? Are you using CES’ mailing services to reach attendees before, during and after the event? Are you utilizing our award-winning SmartBooth product? Do you have a product to enter in the Innovations 2008 Design and Engineering Awards?</P>
<P>When thinking through these questions, you first need to determine your target audience and how best to reach them at CES. If you don’t know how to reach them, then please contact me or your CES account manager. We can take you through a myriad of targeted opportunities that will help you get the most out of your CES investment.</P>
<P>Next, how can you propel your CES experience into a year-round campaign? How else can you leverage your relationship with CES and CEA to touch your target audiences? Are you reaching them at other CEA and CES events? Are you touching them through exposure in<I> Vision</I> magazine? Are you using all the resources CEA provides to members – from market research and informative publications and webcasts to government lobbying and technology standards development? We know for CES to truly be successful for you, it needs to not be just a four-day event, but, instead, an avenue to help you reach your key audiences throughout the year. </P>
<P><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: ">Thank you for your participation at this coming year’s show. We’re thrilled to work with you on this exciting journey. Welcome back to CES.</SPAN></P></p>
